President Obama has nominated Charles M. Oberly, III to serve as U.S. Attorney for the District of Delaware. Oberly has a background in law, having worked for the Delaware Department of Justice from 1975 to 1995 and serving as Attorney General from 1983 to 1995. He has also worked as a partner at various law firms and is currently Of Counsel to Drinker Biddle & Reath LLP. President Obama expressed confidence that Oberly will serve the people of Delaware with distinction. Oberly graduated from Wesley Junior College in 1966, received his bachelor's degree from Pennsylvania State University in 1968, and obtained his J.D. from the University of Virginia School of Law in 1971.